          "FACILITY": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "facility": [
                  "NGEN"
                ],
                "institute": "3CPRNPC"
              },
              "free_text": [
                " K-400 neutron generator at Chinese",
                "Academy of Engineering Physics (CAEP)"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "incident_source": [
                  "D-T"
                ],
                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Neutrons with a yield about 3 to 4E10 n/s were",
                "generated with an effective deuteron beam energy of",
                "136 keV and a beam current of 280 uA. The T-Mo target",
                "used in the generator had a thickness of 0.566 mg/cm2",
                "and an active zone diameter of 1.2 cm."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "nuclide": "34-SE-74",
                "field_identifier": "NAT",
                "value": 0.0089
              },
              "free_text": [
                " 14 g of high purity Se powder",
                "was pressed at 10 ton/cm2, and a pellet of 0.3 cm",
                "thickness and 2.0 cm in diameter was obtained. A",
                "total of three such pellets were prepared. Monitor",
                "foils (Nb, 99.99% pure, 0.5 mm thick) having the same",
                "diameter as the pellets, were then attached in the",
                "front and at the back of each sample."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "ACTIV"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The entire process of irradiation for all the",
                "three samples lasted about 60-90 min. The three",
                "samples were placed at 0, 90, and 135 deg angles",
                "respectively, relative to the beam direction and",
                "centred with respect to the tritium-molybdenum (T-Mo)",
                "target at a distance of about 4 cm."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "HPGE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " A HPGe detector with a relative efficiency of",
                "about 68 % and an energy resolution of 1.69 keV at",
                "1332 keV for 60Co. The distance from sample to",
                "detector was 4.0-8.0 cm. The efficiency of the",
                "detector was pre-calibrated using various standard",
                "gamma sources like Co-57, Co-60, Cd-109, Ba-133,",
                "Cs-137, Eu-152, Am-241, and Ra-226."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SIBAR"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The neutron-flux was monitored by the",
                "accompanying alpha-particles to facilitate",
                "corrections for small variations in the yield. The",
                "Au-Si surface barrier detector used in 135 deg",
                "irradiation accompanying alpha-particle tube was set",
                "at a distance of 110 cm from the tritium target."
              ]
            }
          ],
